snippet: The death of a respected West Bank governor, Qadoura Moussa, is the latest sign that lawlessness is creeping back into Jenin, a beacon of Palestinian self-rule.
abstract: Death of Qadoura Moussa, a respected West Bank governor who died of a heart attack while investigating gunfire directed at his home, is the latest sign that lawlessness has returned to Jenin, a city considered to be a model of Palestinian self-rule.
lead_paragraph: The death of a respected West Bank governor, Qadoura Moussa, is the latest sign that lawlessness is creeping back into Jenin, a beacon of Palestinian self-rule.

headline.seo: Jenin Loses Leader as West Bank Violence Returns
headline.main: Model West Bank City Loses a Crime Fighter
headline.print_headline: A Model City Loses a Crime Fighter
